attributionInfo.brokerName: Better Homes & Gardens SW Grp - Spfld

data.description: Nestled amidst the serene embrace of nature, this exceptional 4-bedroom, 3-bath Hobby Farm / Estate sprawls across 2,532 square feet and 10 Acres.  Boasting an ideal blend of modern comfort and rustic charm, this property is a haven for those seeking space, luxury, and tranquility.Upon entry, a seamless fusion of the living room and kitchen welcomes you, showcasing an open layout that effortlessly encourages gatherings and seamless entertainment. Adorned with granite and woodblock countertops, the kitchen becomes the heart of the home, complemented by stainless steel appliances.The primary bedroom is a retreat in itself, featuring not one but two generous walk-in closets, offering ample space for organization and indulgence.Ascending the stairs reveals a family room alongside a bonus area, presenting versatility for leisure or recreation. Two additional bedrooms and a full bathroom upstairs provide privacy and comfort for family members or guests.Outside, the property unfolds across a sprawling 10 acres, a blend of partial hay field, wooded areas and a pond that is stocked with catfish, bluegill and crayfish. The landscape serves as a canvas for diverse activities and possibilities, from tranquil walks through wooded trails or for the hobby farm enthusiast.Completing this estate / hobby farm are 5 auxiliary structures that enhance its functionality and appeal. There is a shop for your projects, a horse stable for equine enthusiasts, and a large barn that holds promises of storage or creative endeavors a dairy barn with 8 milking stations set up with an automatic milking system (dairy has not been used by current owners but looks operational) and a chicken coop with 20 nesting boxes to house approx 50 hens, swings and perches! Please note, this property is offered ''as is, no repairs,'' allowing buyers the opportunity to conduct inspections and make this retreat their own.
